## ERGSN — Cloudflare Pages security headers
## ----------------------------------------------------------------
## Active only when the site is served from Cloudflare Pages.
## On GitHub Pages this file is ignored (Pages does not support
## custom HTTP headers). Reference: A-1 from the unsafe-inline /
## frame-ancestors / Cloudflare Pages migration plan.
##
## What this file fixes vs. meta-CSP alone:
##   - `frame-ancestors` is HEADER-ONLY in modern browsers; the same
##     directive in <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"> is
##     silently ignored. So clickjacking defence requires this file.
##   - `Strict-Transport-Security`, `Permissions-Policy`,
##     `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy` are header-only as well.
##
## Other CSP directives (script-src, style-src, connect-src, …)
## remain in each page's <meta> tag because they apply page-by-page
## and we do not want to maintain two sources of truth. Once
## `'unsafe-inline'` is removed (Plan B-1), the script-src / style-src
## hashes can be promoted into the headers below.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=(), interest-cohort=()
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload

## Long-lived cache for fingerprinted build output (will be added when
## esbuild emits hashed filenames into /dist/). Safe even before /dist
## exists — non-matching paths simply fall through.
/dist/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

## Product images are content-addressed by filename; treat as immutable.
/images/products/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
/images/stays/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
